<br>
Likewise the DS hits in the smae instant that the mob does. If the mob just swung, it wasn't mezzed. So, there is no &quot;the DS broke the Mez.&quot; This falls into the same old false notion that a DS helps a tank hold aggro (which it obviously can't because it's nuetral damage).<br>
<br>
There is far to much false information going around and being perpetuated.<br>
<br>
I'd much sooner suggest that these problems are due to lag or other server communication problems than to try to make up reasonable sounding myths to explain why the EQ universe works. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uultravoices.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ultravoices</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(7/11/02 9:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=573.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.brunching.com/images/phonesex-everquest.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets &amp; Mez</span><hr size=1> <br>
