1) Players on the wrong target. (Easily the most often reason. Many times from the main tank changes targets as multiple mobs arrive, with the other players having aquired their /assist on the incoming target, thus all targeting separately, and many of these using a DoT)<br>
2) DoTs on the target. (Many classes will get their DoT spells on the wrong target, either by missing the main tank switching on incoming, or by just not /assisting.) The mes will often 'blur' the mob and thus the mob won't remember the DoTer, and conveniently, neither will the player.<br>
3) Pets on the wrong target. Most pet class players who group a lot have learned how to manage their pets in a group, but there still is the rare one with no clue (former druids and their monk/rogue twinks starting a new pet class twink <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) I trust the new coding, having seen my pet many times mid battle stop fighting the (already engaged) main target when the enchanter uses an AE mez. With water and fire pets, I can see where their damage spell might take a fraction of a second to land, and this (rarely) might break a mez, but should never happen with an earth or air pet. <p>Yizaar deCharme<BR>
