<br>
My point is that you shouldn't argue that your pet never breaks mezzes due to the new pet changes because it's false. The changes are buggy, and the pet will still break mezzes on occasion, however small that chance is. If the enchanter is blaming your pet for a mez break when the pet is sitting in a corner away, you can yell at him all you want, he sucks. That wasn't was I was talking about though.<br>
<br>
Usually good enchanters can tell easily if and how a mez is broken. A mob being dotted is a no-brainer. And if your pet is on a different mob 20-30 feet away from the mob when mez was broken, it's pretty obvious that the pet didn't do it. Your argument wasn't relevant.<br>
<br>
Frankly though, if you don't even understand what breaks a mez reading by your false assumptions, then you really shouldn't tell the enchanter that your pet couldn't possibly be the culprit.  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4356">Turonyen - Level 60 Enchanter</a><br>
